td.div: English: Texas Flag—Come and Take It. This flag was raised by Texas settlers at the Battle of Gonzales in October 1835 after Mexico attempted to retrieve a cannon which had been granted to the town of Gonzales for protection against raids by native tribes.
Español: La bandera "Come and Take It" - El texto dice "Come and Take It!" ("Venga y tome!")
